INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (169,1,'2021-01-19 06:17:54','2021-01-19 01:17:54','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n<h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">LOCAL MENTAL HEALTH RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>Community Perspective in Mental Health</b><br> providing ongoing support through home visits and community actions to people with mental health issues. 514-696-0972<br> www.pcsm-cpmh.org\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Centre Bienvenue</b><br> mental health day centre, provides intervention and referral services to adults suffering from mental illness. Community support,<br> activities, workshops, work training &amp; reintegration. 514-421-2212\n                            www.centrebienvenue.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Crisis Centre</b><br> Short-stay accommodation and psychosocial intervention program for adults suffering from psychological distress in the West Island. 514-<br> 684-6160 www.centredecriseoi.com<br><br>\n                            <b>Equipe Entreprise</b> Employment program for individuals suffering from mental health problems in the culinary field. 514 636-1081 <b>www.equipeentreprise.org</b><br><br>\n                            <b>Friends for Mental Health</b><br> provides essential support as well referral services and respite to families coping with the mental illness of a loved one.<br> 514-636-6885 www.asmfmh.org<br><br>\n                            <b>Omega Community Resources Centre</b><br> offers a day centre and residence; provides services and activities, work training and reintegration to adults suffering from<br> mental health problems. 514-631-2760 Day Centre\n                            / Residences 514 683-7224 <b>www.omegacenter.org</b><br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Citizen Advocacy</b><br> supporting people with mental health problems, providing courses, outreach, apartments, and matching them with competent<br> volunteers. 514-694-5850 <b>volunteerwica.com</b><br><br>\n                            <b>Action Jeunesse de l’Ouest-de-l\'Île (AJOI)</b> offers street/community outreach services, intervention and prevention services<br> for youth aged 12 to 25 at risk and/or in difficulty with the West Island, and WI citizens\n                            of all ages facing homelessness and<br> instability. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info<br><br>\n\n                            <b>IUHSSC Integrated University Health and Social Services Centre - Montréal West Island</b> provides the<br> public with health and social services, includes CLSC Pierrefonds 514-626-2572, CLSC Lac-Saint-Louis 514-697-4110,\n                            CLSC\n                            <br> Lachine-Dorval 514-639-0650, Lakeshore General Hospital 514-630-2225, Outpatient Clinic 514-630-2010, Douglas<br> Hospital 514-761-6131, etc. www.ciusss-ouestmtl.gouv.qc.ca</p>\n<br/>\n<hr/>\n<h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">OTHER LOCAL RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>ABO-VAS</b> W.I. Volunteer Accompaniment Service helps vulnerable West-Island residents who require accompanied-transport to<br> get to their vital medical appointments on the Island of Montreal. 514.694.3838 www.abovas.com<br><br>\n                            <b>Action Autonomie</b> Defend &amp; promote rights of consumers, accompaniment, information, etc. 514-525-5060<br> www.actionautonomie.qc.ca\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>AMCAL (Family Services)</b> Residence, development workshops, and other programs for teens. 514-694-3161 www.amcal.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>ANEB Quebec (Anorexia and Bulimia Quebec)</b> provides support to individuals and their families who are affected by eating<br> disorders. 514-630-0907 www.anebquebec.com<br><br>\n                            <b>L’Arrimage</b> is a work integration and job support service for people with severe mental health problems. 514-389-9393<br> www.larrimage.ca\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Avatil</b> A community based organization providing services to those with mild or borderline intellectual handicaps 514-634-8944<br> www.avatil.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Batshaw Youth &amp; Family Center</b> (Youth Protection) Provides psychosocial, rehabilitation and social integration services; to<br> ensure the provision of services related to child placement, adoption, adoption disclosure,\n                            reunification, expertise to the<br> Superior Court and mediation (kids under 18) 514-935-6196<br><br>\n                            <b>CALACS</b> West Island - Phone + emergency support, advocacy, legal info for assaulted women ages 14+. 514-684-2198<br> www.calacsdelouest.ca\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Family Resource Centre</b> supports families with children, teenagers and young adults experiencing academic difficulties.<br> Social/study skills program (ages 4-17), school advocacy, family counseling. 514-685-5912 familyresourcecenter.qc.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Leave Out Violence</b> Anti-violence programs through media arts, positive life skills workshops. 514-938-0006<br> leaveoutviolence.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>SOS Violence conjugale</b> Provide women victims of domestic violence in the province of Quebec telephone support,<br> assessment and referral, 24/7. 1 800 363-9010 www.sosviolenceconjugale.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>Volunteer West Island</b> provides seniors experiencing a loss of autonomy with the opportunity to live at home through Meals on<br> Wheels and a home support services. Also opportunities for anyone to do volunteering\n                            in the community 514-457-5445<br> www.cabouestdelile.org\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>WIAIH</b> West Island Association for the Intellectually Handicapped - Increase opportunities for individuals with intellectual<br> disabilities or autism, strengthen their families and sensitize the community. (514) 316-9017\n                            wiaih.qc.ca/\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Assistance Fund</b> Provide clients with food and whenever the need arises, also give out furniture, household<br> goods and clothing 514-683-0456 fdoi.org<br><br>\n                            <b>West Island CJE</b> along with its partners, supports young adults through programs such as social reintegration, job search,<br> returning to school and entrepreneurship. 514-782-0433 www.cjeouestile.qc.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>West Island Community Resource Centre</b> is a bilingual resource service providing valuable information on health and social<br> and community services. 514-694-6404 www.crcinfo.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>West Island Women’s Shelter</b> Activities, support groups, workshops, special programs for teens &amp; mothers 514-695-8529\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Aide</b> Free, anonymous, &amp; non-judgmental listening centre for people in distress. 514-935-1101\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Aines</b> Free, anonymous, and confidential listening line for 60+. 514-353-2463\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Ecoute</b> Free, confidential, &amp; anonymous listening line for people who need to talk. 514-493-4512\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Jeunes</b> 24/7 support and helpline &amp; phone counseling for kids and teens. 514-263-2266\n                        </p>\n<br/>\n<hr/>\n  <h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">OTHER MENTAL HEALTH RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>AGIDD-SMQ</b> Info, defends the rights of mentally ill individuals, works w/ministries. 514-523-3443 agidd.org<br><br>\n\n                            <b>AMI-Quebec</b> Peer support groups for consumers &amp; families, education, referrals, etc. 514-486-1448 amiquebec.org<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Association Canadienne pour la Santé Mentale (Montreal)</b> Resources, publications, referrals to local services. 514-521-4993<br> acsmmontreal.qc.ca\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Canadian Mental Health Association – Quebec</b> Resources, publications, referrals to local services 514-849-3291 cmha.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Centre for Addiction and Mental Health</b> Info on addiction and mental health 1 800 463-2338<br><br>\n                            <b>Déprimes Anonymes</b> Listening line Mondays-Fridays 10am-10pm, referrals 514-278-2130<br><br>\n                            <b>National Network for Mental Health</b> information, promoting hope &amp; recovery. nnmh.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>National Alliance for Mentally Ill</b> Information, advocacy, education, various support and programs available 800-950-6264<br><br>\n                            <b>National Institute of Mental Health (NIMH)</b> Outreach, education, publications, research, and statistics, referrals. 1-866-615-<br> 6464 Nimh.nih.gov<br><br>\n                            <b>RACOR</b> Réseau Alternatif et Communautaire des ORganismes (RACOR) en santé mentale de l’île de Montréal - Alternative<br> and Community Network of Organizations in mental health in Montreal, to bring together, support,\n                            equip and represent<br> community and alternative organizations in the region that work in mental health field. 514 847-0787 racorsm.org/en<br><br>\n                            <b>Recovery</b> Anxiety, depression, OCD, schiz., BPD, etc. peer support groups, referrals. 514-481-7030 www.recoverycanada.org<br><br>\n                            <b>Revivre</b> Help-line, education, resources, support groups, counseling – anxiety, depression, bipolar. 1-866-738-4873<br> www.revivre.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Suicide Action Montreal</b> Listening line, education, bereavement support. 1-800-277-3553<br><br>\n                            <b>UP House (Donald Berman)</b> Clubhouse for psychiatric rehabilitation, social &amp; work reintegration, etc. 514-764-5599<br> uphouse.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Wellington Centre</b> (Douglas Hospital) Skill workshops, work reintegration, education, support groups 514-768-2668 x328\n                        </p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">RESSOURCES LOCALES EN SANTÉ MENTALE&lt;/h1>\n                        &lt;br>\n                        &lt;br>\n                        &lt;p>\n                            &lt;b>Perspective communautaire en santé mentale&lt;/b>&lt;br> Organisme offrant un soutien continu par le biais de visites à domicile et d\'actions communautaires aux personnes aux prises&lt;br> avec des problèmes de santé mentale.\n                            514 696-0972 www.pcsm-cpmh.org\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Centre Bienvenue&lt;/b>&lt;br> centre de jour en santé mentale, fournit des services d’intervention et d’aiguillage aux adultes atteints de maladie mentale.&lt;br> Soutien communautaire, activités, ateliers, formation professionnelle\n                            et réintégration. 514-421-2212 www.centrebienvenue.org\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Centre de Crise de l\'Ouest de l\'Île&lt;/b>&lt;br> Service d\'hébergement de courte durée et programme d\'intervention psychosociale dédiés aux adultes souffrant de détresse&lt;br> psychologique de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île de Montréal.\n                            514 684-6160 www.centredecriseoi.com\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Équipe Entreprise&lt;/b>&lt;br> Programme d\'emploi pour les individus souffrant de problèmes de santé mentale dans le domaine culinaire. 514 636-1081&lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>www.equipeentreprise.org&lt;/b>\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Les Amis de la santé mentale&lt;/b>&lt;br> fournit un soutien essentiel ainsi que des services d\'orientation et de répit aux familles aux prises avec la maladie mentale d\'un&lt;br> être cher. 514 636-6885 www.asmfmh.org&lt;br>&lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Omega Centre&lt;/b>&lt;br> offre un centre de jour et une résidence; offre des services et des activités, une formation professionnelle et une réintégration&lt;br> aux adultes souffrant de problèmes de santé mentale. Centre de\n                            jour: 514 631-2760 Résidences Omega: 514 683-7224&lt;br> www.omegacenter.org\n                            &lt;br>&lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Parrainage civique de la banlieue ouest&lt;/b>&lt;br> soutenir les personnes ayant des problèmes de santé mentale, leur proposer des cours, des activités, des appartements, et les&lt;br> jumeler avec des volontaires compétents.\n                            514 694-5850 &lt;b>volunteerwica.com&lt;/b>&lt;br>&lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Action Jeunesse de l’Ouest-de-l\'Île&lt;/b>\n                            &lt;br>&lt;b>(AJOI)&lt;/b>&lt;br> offre des services de proximité, d\'intervention et de prévention dans les rues et les communautés aux jeunes de 12 à 25 ans à risque et / ou en difficulté dans l\'ouest de l\'île, ainsi qu\'aux citoyens\n                            de tout âge confrontés au sans-abrisme et à l\'instabilité. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info offre des services de proximité, d\'intervention et de prévention dans les rues et les communautés aux jeunes de 12 à 25&lt;br> ans à risque\n                            et / ou en difficulté dans l\'ouest de l\'île, ainsi qu\'aux citoyens de tout âge confrontés au sans-abrisme et&lt;br> à l\'instabilité. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info&lt;br>&lt;br>\n\n                            &lt;b>CIUSSS-ODI Centre intégré universitaire de santé et de services sociaux de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île-de-Montréal&lt;/b>&lt;br> fournit au public des services de santé et des services sociaux, incluant CLSC Pierrefonds 514-626-2572, CLSC\n                            Lac-Saint-Louis\n                            &lt;br> 514-697-4110, CLSC Lachine-Dorval 514-639-0650, Hôpital général Lakeshore 514-630-2225, Clinique externe 514-630-2010,&lt;br> Hôpital Douglas 514-761-6131, etc. &lt;b>www.ciusss-ouestmtl.gouv.qc.ca&lt;/b>&lt;/p></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->{:}','{:en}MHCR{:}{:fr}RPCM{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','33-revision-v1','','','2021-01-19 06:17:54','2021-01-19 01:17:54','',33,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/33-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (170,1,'2021-01-19 06:22:55','2021-01-19 01:22:55','','','','inherit','closed','closed','','107-revision-v1','','','2021-01-19 06:22:55','2021-01-19 01:22:55','',107,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/107-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (171,1,'2021-01-19 06:25:40','2021-01-19 01:25:40','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n<h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">LOCAL MENTAL HEALTH RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>Community Perspective in Mental Health</b><br> providing ongoing support through home visits and community actions to people with mental health issues. 514-696-0972<br> www.pcsm-cpmh.org\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Centre Bienvenue</b><br> mental health day centre, provides intervention and referral services to adults suffering from mental illness. Community support,<br> activities, workshops, work training &amp; reintegration. 514-421-2212\n                            www.centrebienvenue.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Crisis Centre</b><br> Short-stay accommodation and psychosocial intervention program for adults suffering from psychological distress in the West Island. 514-<br> 684-6160 www.centredecriseoi.com<br><br>\n                            <b>Equipe Entreprise</b> Employment program for individuals suffering from mental health problems in the culinary field. 514 636-1081 <b>www.equipeentreprise.org</b><br><br>\n                            <b>Friends for Mental Health</b><br> provides essential support as well referral services and respite to families coping with the mental illness of a loved one.<br> 514-636-6885 www.asmfmh.org<br><br>\n                            <b>Omega Community Resources Centre</b><br> offers a day centre and residence; provides services and activities, work training and reintegration to adults suffering from<br> mental health problems. 514-631-2760 Day Centre\n                            / Residences 514 683-7224 <b>www.omegacenter.org</b><br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Citizen Advocacy</b><br> supporting people with mental health problems, providing courses, outreach, apartments, and matching them with competent<br> volunteers. 514-694-5850 <b>volunteerwica.com</b><br><br>\n                            <b>Action Jeunesse de l’Ouest-de-l\'Île (AJOI)</b> offers street/community outreach services, intervention and prevention services<br> for youth aged 12 to 25 at risk and/or in difficulty with the West Island, and WI citizens\n                            of all ages facing homelessness and<br> instability. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info<br><br>\n\n                            <b>IUHSSC Integrated University Health and Social Services Centre - Montréal West Island</b> provides the<br> public with health and social services, includes CLSC Pierrefonds 514-626-2572, CLSC Lac-Saint-Louis 514-697-4110,\n                            CLSC\n                            <br> Lachine-Dorval 514-639-0650, Lakeshore General Hospital 514-630-2225, Outpatient Clinic 514-630-2010, Douglas<br> Hospital 514-761-6131, etc. www.ciusss-ouestmtl.gouv.qc.ca</p>\n<br/>\n<hr/>\n<h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">OTHER LOCAL RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>ABO-VAS</b> W.I. Volunteer Accompaniment Service helps vulnerable West-Island residents who require accompanied-transport to<br> get to their vital medical appointments on the Island of Montreal. 514.694.3838 www.abovas.com<br><br>\n                            <b>Action Autonomie</b> Defend &amp; promote rights of consumers, accompaniment, information, etc. 514-525-5060<br> www.actionautonomie.qc.ca\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>AMCAL (Family Services)</b> Residence, development workshops, and other programs for teens. 514-694-3161 www.amcal.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>ANEB Quebec (Anorexia and Bulimia Quebec)</b> provides support to individuals and their families who are affected by eating<br> disorders. 514-630-0907 www.anebquebec.com<br><br>\n                            <b>L’Arrimage</b> is a work integration and job support service for people with severe mental health problems. 514-389-9393<br> www.larrimage.ca\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Avatil</b> A community based organization providing services to those with mild or borderline intellectual handicaps 514-634-8944<br> www.avatil.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Batshaw Youth &amp; Family Center</b> (Youth Protection) Provides psychosocial, rehabilitation and social integration services; to<br> ensure the provision of services related to child placement, adoption, adoption disclosure,\n                            reunification, expertise to the<br> Superior Court and mediation (kids under 18) 514-935-6196<br><br>\n                            <b>CALACS</b> West Island - Phone + emergency support, advocacy, legal info for assaulted women ages 14+. 514-684-2198<br> www.calacsdelouest.ca\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Family Resource Centre</b> supports families with children, teenagers and young adults experiencing academic difficulties.<br> Social/study skills program (ages 4-17), school advocacy, family counseling. 514-685-5912 familyresourcecenter.qc.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Leave Out Violence</b> Anti-violence programs through media arts, positive life skills workshops. 514-938-0006<br> leaveoutviolence.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>SOS Violence conjugale</b> Provide women victims of domestic violence in the province of Quebec telephone support,<br> assessment and referral, 24/7. 1 800 363-9010 www.sosviolenceconjugale.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>Volunteer West Island</b> provides seniors experiencing a loss of autonomy with the opportunity to live at home through Meals on<br> Wheels and a home support services. Also opportunities for anyone to do volunteering\n                            in the community 514-457-5445<br> www.cabouestdelile.org\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>WIAIH</b> West Island Association for the Intellectually Handicapped - Increase opportunities for individuals with intellectual<br> disabilities or autism, strengthen their families and sensitize the community. (514) 316-9017\n                            wiaih.qc.ca/\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Assistance Fund</b> Provide clients with food and whenever the need arises, also give out furniture, household<br> goods and clothing 514-683-0456 fdoi.org<br><br>\n                            <b>West Island CJE</b> along with its partners, supports young adults through programs such as social reintegration, job search,<br> returning to school and entrepreneurship. 514-782-0433 www.cjeouestile.qc.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>West Island Community Resource Centre</b> is a bilingual resource service providing valuable information on health and social<br> and community services. 514-694-6404 www.crcinfo.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>West Island Women’s Shelter</b> Activities, support groups, workshops, special programs for teens &amp; mothers 514-695-8529\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Aide</b> Free, anonymous, &amp; non-judgmental listening centre for people in distress. 514-935-1101\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Aines</b> Free, anonymous, and confidential listening line for 60+. 514-353-2463\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Ecoute</b> Free, confidential, &amp; anonymous listening line for people who need to talk. 514-493-4512\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Jeunes</b> 24/7 support and helpline &amp; phone counseling for kids and teens. 514-263-2266\n                        </p>\n<br/>\n<hr/>\n  <h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">OTHER MENTAL HEALTH RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>AGIDD-SMQ</b> Info, defends the rights of mentally ill individuals, works w/ministries. 514-523-3443 agidd.org<br><br>\n\n                            <b>AMI-Quebec</b> Peer support groups for consumers &amp; families, education, referrals, etc. 514-486-1448 amiquebec.org<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Association Canadienne pour la Santé Mentale (Montreal)</b> Resources, publications, referrals to local services. 514-521-4993<br> acsmmontreal.qc.ca\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Canadian Mental Health Association – Quebec</b> Resources, publications, referrals to local services 514-849-3291 cmha.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Centre for Addiction and Mental Health</b> Info on addiction and mental health 1 800 463-2338<br><br>\n                            <b>Déprimes Anonymes</b> Listening line Mondays-Fridays 10am-10pm, referrals 514-278-2130<br><br>\n                            <b>National Network for Mental Health</b> information, promoting hope &amp; recovery. nnmh.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>National Alliance for Mentally Ill</b> Information, advocacy, education, various support and programs available 800-950-6264<br><br>\n                            <b>National Institute of Mental Health (NIMH)</b> Outreach, education, publications, research, and statistics, referrals. 1-866-615-<br> 6464 Nimh.nih.gov<br><br>\n                            <b>RACOR</b> Réseau Alternatif et Communautaire des ORganismes (RACOR) en santé mentale de l’île de Montréal - Alternative<br> and Community Network of Organizations in mental health in Montreal, to bring together, support,\n                            equip and represent<br> community and alternative organizations in the region that work in mental health field. 514 847-0787 racorsm.org/en<br><br>\n                            <b>Recovery</b> Anxiety, depression, OCD, schiz., BPD, etc. peer support groups, referrals. 514-481-7030 www.recoverycanada.org<br><br>\n                            <b>Revivre</b> Help-line, education, resources, support groups, counseling – anxiety, depression, bipolar. 1-866-738-4873<br> www.revivre.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Suicide Action Montreal</b> Listening line, education, bereavement support. 1-800-277-3553<br><br>\n                            <b>UP House (Donald Berman)</b> Clubhouse for psychiatric rehabilitation, social &amp; work reintegration, etc. 514-764-5599<br> uphouse.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Wellington Centre</b> (Douglas Hospital) Skill workshops, work reintegration, education, support groups 514-768-2668 x328\n                        </p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">RESSOURCES LOCALES EN SANTÉ MENTALE&lt;/h1>\n                        &lt;br>\n                        &lt;br>\n                        &lt;p>\n                            &lt;b>Perspective communautaire en santé mentale&lt;/b>&lt;br> Organisme offrant un soutien continu par le biais de visites à domicile et d\'actions communautaires aux personnes aux prises&lt;br> avec des problèmes de santé mentale.\n                            514 696-0972 www.pcsm-cpmh.org\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Centre Bienvenue&lt;/b>&lt;br> centre de jour en santé mentale, fournit des services d’intervention et d’aiguillage aux adultes atteints de maladie mentale.&lt;br> Soutien communautaire, activités, ateliers, formation professionnelle\n                            et réintégration. 514-421-2212 www.centrebienvenue.org\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Centre de Crise de l\'Ouest de l\'Île&lt;/b>&lt;br> Service d\'hébergement de courte durée et programme d\'intervention psychosociale dédiés aux adultes souffrant de détresse&lt;br> psychologique de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île de Montréal.\n                            514 684-6160 www.centredecriseoi.com\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Équipe Entreprise&lt;/b>&lt;br> Programme d\'emploi pour les individus souffrant de problèmes de santé mentale dans le domaine culinaire. 514 636-1081&lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>www.equipeentreprise.org&lt;/b>\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Les Amis de la santé mentale&lt;/b>&lt;br> fournit un soutien essentiel ainsi que des services d\'orientation et de répit aux familles aux prises avec la maladie mentale d\'un&lt;br> être cher. 514 636-6885 www.asmfmh.org&lt;br>&lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Omega Centre&lt;/b>&lt;br> offre un centre de jour et une résidence; offre des services et des activités, une formation professionnelle et une réintégration&lt;br> aux adultes souffrant de problèmes de santé mentale. Centre de\n                            jour: 514 631-2760 Résidences Omega: 514 683-7224&lt;br> www.omegacenter.org\n                            &lt;br>&lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Parrainage civique de la banlieue ouest&lt;/b>&lt;br> soutenir les personnes ayant des problèmes de santé mentale, leur proposer des cours, des activités, des appartements, et les&lt;br> jumeler avec des volontaires compétents.\n                            514 694-5850 &lt;b>volunteerwica.com&lt;/b>&lt;br>&lt;br>\n                            &lt;b>Action Jeunesse de l’Ouest-de-l\'Île&lt;/b>\n                            &lt;br>&lt;b>(AJOI)&lt;/b>&lt;br> offre des services de proximité, d\'intervention et de prévention dans les rues et les communautés aux jeunes de 12 à 25 ans à risque et / ou en difficulté dans l\'ouest de l\'île, ainsi qu\'aux citoyens\n                            de tout âge confrontés au sans-abrisme et à l\'instabilité. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info offre des services de proximité, d\'intervention et de prévention dans les rues et les communautés aux jeunes de 12 à 25&lt;br> ans à risque\n                            et / ou en difficulté dans l\'ouest de l\'île, ainsi qu\'aux citoyens de tout âge confrontés au sans-abrisme et&lt;br> à l\'instabilité. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info&lt;br>&lt;br>\n\n                            &lt;b>CIUSSS-ODI Centre intégré universitaire de santé et de services sociaux de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île-de-Montréal&lt;/b>&lt;br> fournit au public des services de santé et des services sociaux, incluant CLSC Pierrefonds 514-626-2572, CLSC\n                            Lac-Saint-Louis\n                            &lt;br> 514-697-4110, CLSC Lachine-Dorval 514-639-0650, Hôpital général Lakeshore 514-630-2225, Clinique externe 514-630-2010,&lt;br> Hôpital Douglas 514-761-6131, etc. &lt;b>www.ciusss-ouestmtl.gouv.qc.ca&lt;/b>&lt;/p></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->{:}','{:en}Mental Health Community Resources{:}{:fr}Resources Communautaires En Santé Mentale{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','33-revision-v1','','','2021-01-19 06:25:40','2021-01-19 01:25:40','',33,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/qc/33-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (172,1,'2021-01-19 06:26:53','2021-01-19 01:26:53','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n<br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>CIUSSS-ODI - Centre intégré universitaire de santé et de services sociaux de l’Ouest-de-l’Île-de-Montréal<br> PCSM - Perspective Communautaire en Santé Mentale<br> CB - Centre Bienvenue<br> CCOI - Centre de crise de l\'Ouest\n                            de l\'Île\n                            <br> EE - Équipe Entreprise<br> FMH - Les Amis de la santé mentale<br> WICA - Parrainage Civique de la Banlieue Ouest<br> AJOI - Action Jeunesse De L\'Ouest De L\'Île\n                        </p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">WICG Partners/Supporters&lt;/h1>\n                        &lt;br>\n                        &lt;br>\n                        &lt;p>CIUSSS-ODI - Centre intégré universitaire de santé et de services sociaux de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île-de-Montréal\n                            &lt;br> PCSM - Community Perspective in Mental Health\n                            &lt;br> CB - Centre Bienvenue\n                            &lt;br> CCOI - West Island Crisis Centre\n                            &lt;br> EE - Equipe Entreprise\n                            &lt;br> FMH - Friends for Mental Health\n                            &lt;br> WICA - West Island Citizen Advocacy\n                            &lt;br> AJOI - Action Jeunesse de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Ile\n                            &lt;br>\n                            &lt;br> Thank you all for your much appreciated support and involvement!\n                        &lt;/p></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->{:}','{:en}Community Partners{:}{:fr}Partenaires et Supporters{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','46-revision-v1','','','2021-01-19 06:26:53','2021-01-19 01:26:53','',46,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/qc/46-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (173,1,'2021-01-19 06:29:13','2021-01-19 01:29:13','','{:en}News And Events{:}{:fr}Nouvelles et Événements{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','107-revision-v1','','','2021-01-19 06:29:13','2021-01-19 01:29:13','',107,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/qc/107-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (175,1,'2021-01-20 02:48:21','2021-01-19 21:48:21','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n<p>\n                                </p><li>To promote the participation and empowerment of our peers dealing with mental health issues, topics or questions that concern them.</li>\n                                <li>To raise awareness and sensitize the public to the reality of people living with or have lived a mental illness.</li>\n                                <li>To fight the stigma of mental illness and to promote recovery and advocate for better services.</li>\n                        <p></p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;p>                            &lt;/p>&lt;ul>                                &lt;li>Promouvoir la participation et l\'autonomisation de nos pairs traitant de problèmes de santé mentale, de sujets ou de questions qui les concernent.&lt;/li>                                &lt;li>Informer et sensibiliser le public à la réalité des personnes vivant avec ou ayant vécu une maladie mentale.&lt;/li>                                &lt;li>Lutter contre la stigmatisation liée à la maladie mentale, promouvoir le rétablissement et plaider en faveur de meilleurs services.                            &lt;/li>&lt;/ul>                        &lt;p>&lt;/p></code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->{:}','{:en}Our Goals{:}{:fr}Nos Buts{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','7-revision-v1','','','2021-01-20 02:48:21','2021-01-19 21:48:21','',7,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/7-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (176,1,'2021-01-20 04:08:13','2021-01-19 23:08:13','<!-- wp:heading --><h2>Who we are</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>Our website address is: http://wicg-website.local.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>What personal data we collect and why we collect it</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Comments</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>When visitors leave comments on the site we collect the data shown in the comments form, and also the visitor&#8217;s IP address and browser user agent string to help spam detection.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Media</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Contact forms</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Cookies</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you visit our login page, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select &quot;Remember Me&quot;, your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Embedded content from other websites</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Analytics</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Who we share your data with</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you request a password reset, your IP address will be included in the reset email.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>How long we retain your data</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>What rights you have over your data</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Where we send your data</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:paragraph --><p>Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.</p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Your contact information</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading --><h2>Additional information</h2><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>How we protect your data</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>What data breach procedures we have in place</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>What third parties we receive data from</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>What automated decision making and/or profiling we do with user data</h3><!-- /wp:heading --><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} --><h3>Industry regulatory disclosure requirements</h3><!-- /wp:heading -->','Privacy Policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','3-revision-v1','','','2021-01-20 04:08:13','2021-01-19 23:08:13','',3,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/qc/3-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (179,1,'2021-01-22 22:54:57','2021-01-22 17:54:57','<!-- wp:html -->\n<!-- purple x moss 2020 -->\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"{{ str_replace(\'_\', \'-\', app()->getLocale()) }}\">\n\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n    <meta name=\"authors\" content=\"François Dionne, Aleks Uher\">\n    <script src=\"https://use.fontawesome.com/4476535a43.js\"></script>\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.0/css/bootstrap.min.css\">\n    <script src=\"https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.5.1/jquery.min.js\"></script>\n    <script src=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/popper.js/1.16.0/umd/popper.min.js\"></script>\n    <script src=\"https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.5.0/js/bootstrap.min.js\"></script>\n    <title>WICG - 404 Not Found</title>\n</head>\n\n<body>\n    <div class=\"body1\">\n        <div class=\"mainbox\">\n            <div class=\"err\">4</div>\n            <i class=\"far fa-question-circle fa-spin\"></i>\n            <div class=\"err2\">4</div>\n            <br />\n            <div class=\"msg\">Maybe this page moved? Got deleted? Is hiding out in quarantine? Never existed in the first place?\n                <p>Let\'s go <a href=\"<?php echo site_url() ?>\">home</a> and try from there.</p>\n            </div>\n            <br />\n            <p>If you need technical assistance, send us an e-mail: <a href=\"mailto:AleksUher@hotmail.com\">Click Here To Email Us</a></p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</body>\n\n</html>\n<!-- /wp:html -->','{:en}404WICG{:}{:fr}404WICG{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','58-revision-v1','','','2021-01-22 22:54:57','2021-01-22 17:54:57','',58,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/58-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (181,1,'2021-01-22 23:02:41','2021-01-22 18:02:41','<!-- wp:html /-->','{:en}404WICG{:}{:fr}404WICG{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','58-revision-v1','','','2021-01-22 23:02:41','2021-01-22 18:02:41','',58,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/58-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (182,1,'2021-01-22 23:47:09','2021-01-22 18:47:09','{:en}<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are looking for new members who have an interest in sharing their lived experiences in illness and recovery, and are willing, in line with our mission, goals and values, to be actively involved and contribute to making a difference!\n                            New members can be active in attending regular group meetings (usually biweekly, on Saturday afternoons), or can participate from the sidelines via email or telephone.\n                            <br>\n                            <br> New members \'qualify\' by living with, or having lived, a mental health issue. If you wish to become a member of the West Island Citizens Group, contact us and a simple form will be provided to you to fill out and submit\n                            before you attend your first meeting. That way we can get to know you a bit better, your interests and abilities and what strengths you can add to the group!\n                            <br>\n                            <br> If you are interested in joining our dynamic and impactful group of your concerned peers and motivated volunteers, or just want more information about us and what we do, or just want to help us out or support us in any\n                            way, please feel free to contact us! By email at gcoi.wicg@gmail.com, or by phone at 514-636-9952</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:code -->\n<br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>Nous recherchons de nouveaux membres intéressés à partager leurs expériences vécus de maladie et de rétablissement en santé mentale. Ces personnes doivent adhérer à notre mission, objectifs et valeurs, ainsi que participer et contribuer\n                            à faire la différence! Les nouveaux membres peuvent participer activement en assistant aux réunions régulières du groupe (généralement toutes les deux semaines, le samedi après-midi), ou contribuer par courriel ou par téléphone.\n                            Pour devenir membre vous devez vivre avec ou ayant vécu un trouble de santé mentale.\n\n                            <br> Si cela vous intéresse, contactez-nous et un formulaire vous sera fourni, pour compléter et soumettre avant d\'assister à votre première réunion. Ainsi, nous pourrons connaître un peu plus vos intérêts et vos capacités,\n                            ainsi que les atouts que vous pourrez amener au groupe! Si vous êtes intéressé à rejoindre notre groupe dynamique et percutant, composé de membres bénévoles motivés, n\'hésitez pas à nous contacter ! Par courriel à gcoi.wicg@gmail.com\n                            ou par téléphone au 514-636-9952.\n                        </p>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}','{:en}Becoming a Member{:}{:fr}Devenir Membre{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','5-revision-v1','','','2021-01-22 23:47:09','2021-01-22 18:47:09','',5,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/5-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
