INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (195,1,'2021-01-22 23:58:37','2021-01-22 18:58:37','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>If you want more information about us and what we do, or just want to help us out or support us in any way, or if you are interested in joining our group, please contact us!\n                            <br> - Email - gcoi.wicg@gmail.com<br> - Tel (voicemail) – 514-636-9952<br> - facebook.com/wicg.gcoi<br> - Mail: WICG c/o Community Perspective in Mental Health<br> 16115, Boul. Gouin Ouest, bureau 300,<br> Sainte-Geneviève,\n                            Que. H9H 1C7\n                        </p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Si vous souhaitez plus d\'informations sur nous et sur ce que nous faisons, ou si vous souhaitez simplement nous aider ou nous soutenir de quelque manière que ce soit, ou si vous êtes intéressée à rejoindre notre groupe, n\'hésitez pas à nous contacter!<br><br>- Email - gcoi.wicg@gmail.com<br>- Téléphone (messagerie vocale) – 514-636-9952<br>- facebook.com/wicg.gcoi<br>- Mail: GCOI a/s Perspective Communautaire en Santé Mentale<br>16115, Boul. Gouin Ouest, bureau 300,<br>Sainte-Geneviève, Que. H9H 1C7</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}','{:en}Contact Info{:}{:fr}Info Contact{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','23-revision-v1','','','2021-01-22 23:58:37','2021-01-22 18:58:37','',23,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/23-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (197,1,'2021-01-23 00:01:35','2021-01-22 19:01:35','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n<h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">Donations</h1>\n                        <br />\n                        <br />\n                        <p>Thank you for your consideration in supporting us and an important cause. Your donation will go towards furthering our mission & goals, to help raise awareness and fight the stigma of mental illness, and to expand & provide more\n                            outreach for our group, and also to further train new members to our group to use our collective voice in the community!\n                            <br />\n                            <br /> Donations to our West Island Citizens Group can be made via our fiduciary, PCSM, who will issue tax receipts.\n                            <br /> Please make cheques payable to \'Community Perspective in Mental Health\', and\n                            <i>please clearly write \'For the West Island Citizens Group\' on the cheque memo line.</i> Cheques can be given directly to one of our group members, or can be mailed to:\n                            <br /> WICG c/o Community Perspective in Mental Health\n                            <br /> 15795, Boul. Gouin Ouest, 2nd floor,\n                            <br /> Sainte-Genevieve, Que. H9H 1C5\n                            <br /> This is PCSM’s contact info:\n                            <br /> T 514-696-0972 F 514-696-0982\n                            <br /> info@pcsm-cpmh.org / www.pcsm-cpmh.org / www.facebook.com/PCSMCPMH\n                            <br /> Numero de charite 11945 0757 RR 0001 NEQ - 114 216 7262</p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Merci de votre considération pour votre soutien à cette cause importante. Votre don servira à renforcer notre mission et nos objectifs, à contribuer à la sensibilisation, à lutter contre la stigmatisation de la maladie mentale,\n                            ainsi qu’à élargir la portée de notre groupe et à former davantage de nouveaux membres à utiliser notre voix collective dans la communauté!\n                            <br>\n                            <br> Les dons à notre Groupe Citoyen de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île peuvent se faire à travers notre fiduciaire Perspective Communautaire en Santé Mentale, qui pourra émettre un reçu d’impôt de charité au besoin. Veuillez, s’il vous\n                            plait, faire votre chèque au nom de \'Perspective Communautaire en Santé Mentale\' et écrire clairement sur la ligne de notification du chèque: ‘Fonds pour le Groupe Citoyen de l’Ouest-de-l’Île’.\n                            <br> Les chèques peuvent être remis directement à l’un des membres de notre groupe, ou par envoi postal à:<br> GCOI a/s Perspective Communautaire en Santé Mentale<br> 15795, Boul. Gouin Ouest, 2ième étage,\n                            <br>Sainte-Geneviève, Que. H9H 1C5<br><br> Voici les coordonnées de PCSM:<br> T 514-696-0972 F 514-696-0982<br> info@pcsm-cpmh.org / http://www.pcsm-cpmh.org / www.facebook.com/PCSMCPMH<br> Numéro de charité 11945\n                            0757 RR 0001 NEQ# 114 216 7262\n\n                        </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}','{:en}Donations{:}{:fr}Dons{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','27-revision-v1','','','2021-01-23 00:01:35','2021-01-22 19:01:35','',27,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/27-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (199,1,'2021-01-23 00:05:33','2021-01-22 19:05:33','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n<h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">LOCAL MENTAL HEALTH RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>Community Perspective in Mental Health</b><br> providing ongoing support through home visits and community actions to people with mental health issues. 514-696-0972<br> www.pcsm-cpmh.org\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Centre Bienvenue</b><br> mental health day centre, provides intervention and referral services to adults suffering from mental illness. Community support,<br> activities, workshops, work training &amp; reintegration. 514-421-2212\n                            www.centrebienvenue.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Crisis Centre</b><br> Short-stay accommodation and psychosocial intervention program for adults suffering from psychological distress in the West Island. 514-<br> 684-6160 www.centredecriseoi.com<br><br>\n                            <b>Equipe Entreprise</b> Employment program for individuals suffering from mental health problems in the culinary field. 514 636-1081 <b>www.equipeentreprise.org</b><br><br>\n                            <b>Friends for Mental Health</b><br> provides essential support as well referral services and respite to families coping with the mental illness of a loved one.<br> 514-636-6885 www.asmfmh.org<br><br>\n                            <b>Omega Community Resources Centre</b><br> offers a day centre and residence; provides services and activities, work training and reintegration to adults suffering from<br> mental health problems. 514-631-2760 Day Centre\n                            / Residences 514 683-7224 <b>www.omegacenter.org</b><br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Citizen Advocacy</b><br> supporting people with mental health problems, providing courses, outreach, apartments, and matching them with competent<br> volunteers. 514-694-5850 <b>volunteerwica.com</b><br><br>\n                            <b>Action Jeunesse de l’Ouest-de-l\'Île (AJOI)</b> offers street/community outreach services, intervention and prevention services<br> for youth aged 12 to 25 at risk and/or in difficulty with the West Island, and WI citizens\n                            of all ages facing homelessness and<br> instability. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info<br><br>\n\n                            <b>IUHSSC Integrated University Health and Social Services Centre - Montréal West Island</b> provides the<br> public with health and social services, includes CLSC Pierrefonds 514-626-2572, CLSC Lac-Saint-Louis 514-697-4110,\n                            CLSC\n                            <br> Lachine-Dorval 514-639-0650, Lakeshore General Hospital 514-630-2225, Outpatient Clinic 514-630-2010, Douglas<br> Hospital 514-761-6131, etc. www.ciusss-ouestmtl.gouv.qc.ca</p>\n<br/>\n<hr/>\n<h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">OTHER LOCAL RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>ABO-VAS</b> W.I. Volunteer Accompaniment Service helps vulnerable West-Island residents who require accompanied-transport to<br> get to their vital medical appointments on the Island of Montreal. 514.694.3838 www.abovas.com<br><br>\n                            <b>Action Autonomie</b> Defend &amp; promote rights of consumers, accompaniment, information, etc. 514-525-5060<br> www.actionautonomie.qc.ca\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>AMCAL (Family Services)</b> Residence, development workshops, and other programs for teens. 514-694-3161 www.amcal.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>ANEB Quebec (Anorexia and Bulimia Quebec)</b> provides support to individuals and their families who are affected by eating<br> disorders. 514-630-0907 www.anebquebec.com<br><br>\n                            <b>L’Arrimage</b> is a work integration and job support service for people with severe mental health problems. 514-389-9393<br> www.larrimage.ca\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Avatil</b> A community based organization providing services to those with mild or borderline intellectual handicaps 514-634-8944<br> www.avatil.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Batshaw Youth &amp; Family Center</b> (Youth Protection) Provides psychosocial, rehabilitation and social integration services; to<br> ensure the provision of services related to child placement, adoption, adoption disclosure,\n                            reunification, expertise to the<br> Superior Court and mediation (kids under 18) 514-935-6196<br><br>\n                            <b>CALACS</b> West Island - Phone + emergency support, advocacy, legal info for assaulted women ages 14+. 514-684-2198<br> www.calacsdelouest.ca\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Family Resource Centre</b> supports families with children, teenagers and young adults experiencing academic difficulties.<br> Social/study skills program (ages 4-17), school advocacy, family counseling. 514-685-5912 familyresourcecenter.qc.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Leave Out Violence</b> Anti-violence programs through media arts, positive life skills workshops. 514-938-0006<br> leaveoutviolence.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>SOS Violence conjugale</b> Provide women victims of domestic violence in the province of Quebec telephone support,<br> assessment and referral, 24/7. 1 800 363-9010 www.sosviolenceconjugale.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>Volunteer West Island</b> provides seniors experiencing a loss of autonomy with the opportunity to live at home through Meals on<br> Wheels and a home support services. Also opportunities for anyone to do volunteering\n                            in the community 514-457-5445<br> www.cabouestdelile.org\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>WIAIH</b> West Island Association for the Intellectually Handicapped - Increase opportunities for individuals with intellectual<br> disabilities or autism, strengthen their families and sensitize the community. (514) 316-9017\n                            wiaih.qc.ca/\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Assistance Fund</b> Provide clients with food and whenever the need arises, also give out furniture, household<br> goods and clothing 514-683-0456 fdoi.org<br><br>\n                            <b>West Island CJE</b> along with its partners, supports young adults through programs such as social reintegration, job search,<br> returning to school and entrepreneurship. 514-782-0433 www.cjeouestile.qc.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>West Island Community Resource Centre</b> is a bilingual resource service providing valuable information on health and social<br> and community services. 514-694-6404 www.crcinfo.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>West Island Women’s Shelter</b> Activities, support groups, workshops, special programs for teens &amp; mothers 514-695-8529\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Aide</b> Free, anonymous, &amp; non-judgmental listening centre for people in distress. 514-935-1101\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Aines</b> Free, anonymous, and confidential listening line for 60+. 514-353-2463\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Ecoute</b> Free, confidential, &amp; anonymous listening line for people who need to talk. 514-493-4512\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Jeunes</b> 24/7 support and helpline &amp; phone counseling for kids and teens. 514-263-2266\n                        </p>\n<br/>\n<hr/>\n  <h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">OTHER MENTAL HEALTH RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>AGIDD-SMQ</b> Info, defends the rights of mentally ill individuals, works w/ministries. 514-523-3443 agidd.org<br><br>\n\n                            <b>AMI-Quebec</b> Peer support groups for consumers &amp; families, education, referrals, etc. 514-486-1448 amiquebec.org<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Association Canadienne pour la Santé Mentale (Montreal)</b> Resources, publications, referrals to local services. 514-521-4993<br> acsmmontreal.qc.ca\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Canadian Mental Health Association – Quebec</b> Resources, publications, referrals to local services 514-849-3291 cmha.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Centre for Addiction and Mental Health</b> Info on addiction and mental health 1 800 463-2338<br><br>\n                            <b>Déprimes Anonymes</b> Listening line Mondays-Fridays 10am-10pm, referrals 514-278-2130<br><br>\n                            <b>National Network for Mental Health</b> information, promoting hope &amp; recovery. nnmh.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>National Alliance for Mentally Ill</b> Information, advocacy, education, various support and programs available 800-950-6264<br><br>\n                            <b>National Institute of Mental Health (NIMH)</b> Outreach, education, publications, research, and statistics, referrals. 1-866-615-<br> 6464 Nimh.nih.gov<br><br>\n                            <b>RACOR</b> Réseau Alternatif et Communautaire des ORganismes (RACOR) en santé mentale de l’île de Montréal - Alternative<br> and Community Network of Organizations in mental health in Montreal, to bring together, support,\n                            equip and represent<br> community and alternative organizations in the region that work in mental health field. 514 847-0787 racorsm.org/en<br><br>\n                            <b>Recovery</b> Anxiety, depression, OCD, schiz., BPD, etc. peer support groups, referrals. 514-481-7030 www.recoverycanada.org<br><br>\n                            <b>Revivre</b> Help-line, education, resources, support groups, counseling – anxiety, depression, bipolar. 1-866-738-4873<br> www.revivre.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Suicide Action Montreal</b> Listening line, education, bereavement support. 1-800-277-3553<br><br>\n                            <b>UP House (Donald Berman)</b> Clubhouse for psychiatric rehabilitation, social &amp; work reintegration, etc. 514-764-5599<br> uphouse.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Wellington Centre</b> (Douglas Hospital) Skill workshops, work reintegration, education, support groups 514-768-2668 x328\n                        </p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br><strong>Perspective communautaire en santé mentale</strong><br>Organisme offrant un soutien continu par le biais de visites à domicile et d\'actions communautaires aux personnes aux prises<br>avec des problèmes de santé mentale.<br>514 696-0972 www.pcsm-cpmh.org<br><br><br><br><br><strong>Centre Bienvenue</strong><br>centre de jour en santé mentale, fournit des services d’intervention et d’aiguillage aux adultes atteints de maladie mentale.<br>Soutien communautaire, activités, ateliers, formation professionnelle<br>et réintégration. 514-421-2212 www.centrebienvenue.org<br><br><br><br><br><strong>Centre de Crise de l\'Ouest de l\'Île</strong><br>Service d\'hébergement de courte durée et programme d\'intervention psychosociale dédiés aux adultes souffrant de détresse<br>psychologique de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île de Montréal.<br>514 684-6160 www.centredecriseoi.com<br><br><br><br><br><strong>Équipe Entreprise</strong><br>Programme d\'emploi pour les individus souffrant de problèmes de santé mentale dans le domaine culinaire. 514 636-1081<br><br><strong>www.equipeentreprise.org</strong><br><br><br><br><br><strong>Les Amis de la santé mentale</strong><br>fournit un soutien essentiel ainsi que des services d\'orientation et de répit aux familles aux prises avec la maladie mentale d\'un<br>être cher. 514 636-6885 www.asmfmh.org<br><br><br><strong>Omega Centre</strong><br>offre un centre de jour et une résidence; offre des services et des activités, une formation professionnelle et une réintégration<br>aux adultes souffrant de problèmes de santé mentale. Centre de<br>jour: 514 631-2760 Résidences Omega: 514 683-7224<br>www.omegacenter.org<br><br><br><br><strong>Parrainage civique de la banlieue ouest</strong><br>soutenir les personnes ayant des problèmes de santé mentale, leur proposer des cours, des activités, des appartements, et les<br>jumeler avec des volontaires compétents.<br>514 694-5850 <strong>volunteerwica.com</strong><br><br><br><strong>Action Jeunesse de l’Ouest-de-l\'Île</strong><br><br><strong>(AJOI)</strong><br>offre des services de proximité, d\'intervention et de prévention dans les rues et les communautés aux jeunes de 12 à 25 ans à risque et / ou en difficulté dans l\'ouest de l\'île, ainsi qu\'aux citoyens<br>de tout âge confrontés au sans-abrisme et à l\'instabilité. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info offre des services de proximité, d\'intervention et de prévention dans les rues et les communautés aux jeunes de 12 à 25<br>ans à risque<br>et / ou en difficulté dans l\'ouest de l\'île, ainsi qu\'aux citoyens de tout âge confrontés au sans-abrisme et<br>à l\'instabilité. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>                        &lt;b&gt;CIUSSS-ODI Centre intégré universitaire de santé et de services sociaux de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île-de-Montréal&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt; fournit au public des services de santé et des services sociaux, incluant CLSC Pierrefonds 514-626-2572, CLSC\n                        Lac-Saint-Louis\n                        &lt;br /&gt; 514-697-4110, CLSC Lachine-Dorval 514-639-0650, Hôpital général Lakeshore 514-630-2225, Clinique externe 514-630-2010,&lt;br /&gt; Hôpital Douglas 514-761-6131, etc. &lt;b&gt;www.ciusss-ouestmtl.gouv.qc.ca&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->{:}','{:en}Mental Health Community Resources{:}{:fr}Resources Communautaires En Santé Mentale{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','33-revision-v1','','','2021-01-23 00:05:33','2021-01-22 19:05:33','',33,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/33-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (201,1,'2021-01-23 00:11:15','2021-01-22 19:11:15','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n<h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">LOCAL MENTAL HEALTH RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>Community Perspective in Mental Health</b><br> providing ongoing support through home visits and community actions to people with mental health issues. 514-696-0972<br> www.pcsm-cpmh.org\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Centre Bienvenue</b><br> mental health day centre, provides intervention and referral services to adults suffering from mental illness. Community support,<br> activities, workshops, work training &amp; reintegration. 514-421-2212\n                            www.centrebienvenue.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Crisis Centre</b><br> Short-stay accommodation and psychosocial intervention program for adults suffering from psychological distress in the West Island. 514-<br> 684-6160 www.centredecriseoi.com<br><br>\n                            <b>Equipe Entreprise</b> Employment program for individuals suffering from mental health problems in the culinary field. 514 636-1081 <b>www.equipeentreprise.org</b><br><br>\n                            <b>Friends for Mental Health</b><br> provides essential support as well referral services and respite to families coping with the mental illness of a loved one.<br> 514-636-6885 www.asmfmh.org<br><br>\n                            <b>Omega Community Resources Centre</b><br> offers a day centre and residence; provides services and activities, work training and reintegration to adults suffering from<br> mental health problems. 514-631-2760 Day Centre\n                            / Residences 514 683-7224 <b>www.omegacenter.org</b><br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Citizen Advocacy</b><br> supporting people with mental health problems, providing courses, outreach, apartments, and matching them with competent<br> volunteers. 514-694-5850 <b>volunteerwica.com</b><br><br>\n                            <b>Action Jeunesse de l’Ouest-de-l\'Île (AJOI)</b> offers street/community outreach services, intervention and prevention services<br> for youth aged 12 to 25 at risk and/or in difficulty with the West Island, and WI citizens\n                            of all ages facing homelessness and<br> instability. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info<br><br>\n\n                            <b>IUHSSC Integrated University Health and Social Services Centre - Montréal West Island</b> provides the<br> public with health and social services, includes CLSC Pierrefonds 514-626-2572, CLSC Lac-Saint-Louis 514-697-4110,\n                            CLSC\n                            <br> Lachine-Dorval 514-639-0650, Lakeshore General Hospital 514-630-2225, Outpatient Clinic 514-630-2010, Douglas<br> Hospital 514-761-6131, etc. www.ciusss-ouestmtl.gouv.qc.ca</p>\n<br/>\n<hr/>\n<h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">OTHER LOCAL RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>ABO-VAS</b> W.I. Volunteer Accompaniment Service helps vulnerable West-Island residents who require accompanied-transport to<br> get to their vital medical appointments on the Island of Montreal. 514.694.3838 www.abovas.com<br><br>\n                            <b>Action Autonomie</b> Defend &amp; promote rights of consumers, accompaniment, information, etc. 514-525-5060<br> www.actionautonomie.qc.ca\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>AMCAL (Family Services)</b> Residence, development workshops, and other programs for teens. 514-694-3161 www.amcal.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>ANEB Quebec (Anorexia and Bulimia Quebec)</b> provides support to individuals and their families who are affected by eating<br> disorders. 514-630-0907 www.anebquebec.com<br><br>\n                            <b>L’Arrimage</b> is a work integration and job support service for people with severe mental health problems. 514-389-9393<br> www.larrimage.ca\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Avatil</b> A community based organization providing services to those with mild or borderline intellectual handicaps 514-634-8944<br> www.avatil.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Batshaw Youth &amp; Family Center</b> (Youth Protection) Provides psychosocial, rehabilitation and social integration services; to<br> ensure the provision of services related to child placement, adoption, adoption disclosure,\n                            reunification, expertise to the<br> Superior Court and mediation (kids under 18) 514-935-6196<br><br>\n                            <b>CALACS</b> West Island - Phone + emergency support, advocacy, legal info for assaulted women ages 14+. 514-684-2198<br> www.calacsdelouest.ca\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Family Resource Centre</b> supports families with children, teenagers and young adults experiencing academic difficulties.<br> Social/study skills program (ages 4-17), school advocacy, family counseling. 514-685-5912 familyresourcecenter.qc.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Leave Out Violence</b> Anti-violence programs through media arts, positive life skills workshops. 514-938-0006<br> leaveoutviolence.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>SOS Violence conjugale</b> Provide women victims of domestic violence in the province of Quebec telephone support,<br> assessment and referral, 24/7. 1 800 363-9010 www.sosviolenceconjugale.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>Volunteer West Island</b> provides seniors experiencing a loss of autonomy with the opportunity to live at home through Meals on<br> Wheels and a home support services. Also opportunities for anyone to do volunteering\n                            in the community 514-457-5445<br> www.cabouestdelile.org\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>WIAIH</b> West Island Association for the Intellectually Handicapped - Increase opportunities for individuals with intellectual<br> disabilities or autism, strengthen their families and sensitize the community. (514) 316-9017\n                            wiaih.qc.ca/\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>West Island Assistance Fund</b> Provide clients with food and whenever the need arises, also give out furniture, household<br> goods and clothing 514-683-0456 fdoi.org<br><br>\n                            <b>West Island CJE</b> along with its partners, supports young adults through programs such as social reintegration, job search,<br> returning to school and entrepreneurship. 514-782-0433 www.cjeouestile.qc.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>West Island Community Resource Centre</b> is a bilingual resource service providing valuable information on health and social<br> and community services. 514-694-6404 www.crcinfo.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>West Island Women’s Shelter</b> Activities, support groups, workshops, special programs for teens &amp; mothers 514-695-8529\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Aide</b> Free, anonymous, &amp; non-judgmental listening centre for people in distress. 514-935-1101\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Aines</b> Free, anonymous, and confidential listening line for 60+. 514-353-2463\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Ecoute</b> Free, confidential, &amp; anonymous listening line for people who need to talk. 514-493-4512\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Tel-Jeunes</b> 24/7 support and helpline &amp; phone counseling for kids and teens. 514-263-2266\n                        </p>\n<br/>\n<hr/>\n  <h1 class=\"font-weight-light\">OTHER MENTAL HEALTH RESOURCES</h1>\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>\n                            <b>AGIDD-SMQ</b> Info, defends the rights of mentally ill individuals, works w/ministries. 514-523-3443 agidd.org<br><br>\n\n                            <b>AMI-Quebec</b> Peer support groups for consumers &amp; families, education, referrals, etc. 514-486-1448 amiquebec.org<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Association Canadienne pour la Santé Mentale (Montreal)</b> Resources, publications, referrals to local services. 514-521-4993<br> acsmmontreal.qc.ca\n                            <br><br>\n\n                            <b>Canadian Mental Health Association – Quebec</b> Resources, publications, referrals to local services 514-849-3291 cmha.ca<br><br>\n\n                            <b>Centre for Addiction and Mental Health</b> Info on addiction and mental health 1 800 463-2338<br><br>\n                            <b>Déprimes Anonymes</b> Listening line Mondays-Fridays 10am-10pm, referrals 514-278-2130<br><br>\n                            <b>National Network for Mental Health</b> information, promoting hope &amp; recovery. nnmh.ca<br><br>\n                            <b>National Alliance for Mentally Ill</b> Information, advocacy, education, various support and programs available 800-950-6264<br><br>\n                            <b>National Institute of Mental Health (NIMH)</b> Outreach, education, publications, research, and statistics, referrals. 1-866-615-<br> 6464 Nimh.nih.gov<br><br>\n                            <b>RACOR</b> Réseau Alternatif et Communautaire des ORganismes (RACOR) en santé mentale de l’île de Montréal - Alternative<br> and Community Network of Organizations in mental health in Montreal, to bring together, support,\n                            equip and represent<br> community and alternative organizations in the region that work in mental health field. 514 847-0787 racorsm.org/en<br><br>\n                            <b>Recovery</b> Anxiety, depression, OCD, schiz., BPD, etc. peer support groups, referrals. 514-481-7030 www.recoverycanada.org<br><br>\n                            <b>Revivre</b> Help-line, education, resources, support groups, counseling – anxiety, depression, bipolar. 1-866-738-4873<br> www.revivre.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Suicide Action Montreal</b> Listening line, education, bereavement support. 1-800-277-3553<br><br>\n                            <b>UP House (Donald Berman)</b> Clubhouse for psychiatric rehabilitation, social &amp; work reintegration, etc. 514-764-5599<br> uphouse.org\n                            <br><br>\n                            <b>Wellington Centre</b> (Douglas Hospital) Skill workshops, work reintegration, education, support groups 514-768-2668 x328\n                        </p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br><strong>Perspective communautaire en santé mentale</strong><br>Organisme offrant un soutien continu par le biais de visites à domicile et d\'actions communautaires aux personnes aux prises<br>avec des problèmes de santé mentale.<br>514 696-0972 www.pcsm-cpmh.org<br><br><br><br><br><strong>Centre Bienvenue</strong><br>centre de jour en santé mentale, fournit des services d’intervention et d’aiguillage aux adultes atteints de maladie mentale.<br>Soutien communautaire, activités, ateliers, formation professionnelle<br>et réintégration. 514-421-2212 www.centrebienvenue.org<br><br><br><br><br><strong>Centre de Crise de l\'Ouest de l\'Île</strong><br>Service d\'hébergement de courte durée et programme d\'intervention psychosociale dédiés aux adultes souffrant de détresse<br>psychologique de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île de Montréal.<br>514 684-6160 www.centredecriseoi.com<br><br><br><br><br><strong>Équipe Entreprise</strong><br>Programme d\'emploi pour les individus souffrant de problèmes de santé mentale dans le domaine culinaire. 514 636-1081<br><br><strong>www.equipeentreprise.org</strong><br><br><br><br><br><strong>Les Amis de la santé mentale</strong><br>fournit un soutien essentiel ainsi que des services d\'orientation et de répit aux familles aux prises avec la maladie mentale d\'un<br>être cher. 514 636-6885 www.asmfmh.org<br><br><br><strong>Omega Centre</strong><br>offre un centre de jour et une résidence; offre des services et des activités, une formation professionnelle et une réintégration<br>aux adultes souffrant de problèmes de santé mentale. Centre de<br>jour: 514 631-2760 Résidences Omega: 514 683-7224<br>www.omegacenter.org<br><br><br><br><strong>Parrainage civique de la banlieue ouest</strong><br>soutenir les personnes ayant des problèmes de santé mentale, leur proposer des cours, des activités, des appartements, et les<br>jumeler avec des volontaires compétents.<br>514 694-5850 <strong>volunteerwica.com</strong><br><br><br><strong>Action Jeunesse de l’Ouest-de-l\'Île</strong><br><br><strong>(AJOI)</strong><br>offre des services de proximité, d\'intervention et de prévention dans les rues et les communautés aux jeunes de 12 à 25 ans à risque et / ou en difficulté dans l\'ouest de l\'île, ainsi qu\'aux citoyens<br>de tout âge confrontés au sans-abrisme et à l\'instabilité. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info offre des services de proximité, d\'intervention et de prévention dans les rues et les communautés aux jeunes de 12 à 25<br>ans à risque<br>et / ou en difficulté dans l\'ouest de l\'île, ainsi qu\'aux citoyens de tout âge confrontés au sans-abrisme et<br>à l\'instabilité. 514-674-1270 www.ajoi.info<br><br><br><br><b>CIUSSS-ODI Centre intégré universitaire de santé et de services sociaux de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île-de-Montréal</b><br>fournit au public des services de santé et des services sociaux, incluant CLSC Pierrefonds 514-626-2572, CLSC Lac-Saint-Louis\n<br>514-697-4110, CLSC Lachine-Dorval 514-639-0650, Hôpital général Lakeshore 514-630-2225, Clinique externe 514-630-2010,<br>Hôpital Douglas 514-761-6131, etc. <b>www.ciusss-ouestmtl.gouv.qc.ca</b></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}','{:en}Mental Health Community Resources{:}{:fr}Resources Communautaires En Santé Mentale{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','33-revision-v1','','','2021-01-23 00:11:15','2021-01-22 19:11:15','',33,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/33-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (203,1,'2021-01-23 00:17:44','2021-01-22 19:17:44','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n<p>\n                                </p><li>To promote the participation and empowerment of our peers dealing with mental health issues, topics or questions that concern them.</li>\n                                <li>To raise awareness and sensitize the public to the reality of people living with or have lived a mental illness.</li>\n                                <li>To fight the stigma of mental illness and to promote recovery and advocate for better services.</li>\n                        <p></p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Promouvoir la participation et l\'autonomisation de nos pairs traitant de problèmes de santé mentale, de sujets ou de questions qui les concernent.</li><li>Informer et sensibiliser le public à la réalité des personnes vivant avec ou ayant vécu une maladie mentale.</li><li>Lutter contre la stigmatisation liée à la maladie mentale, promouvoir le rétablissement et plaider en faveur de meilleurs services.</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}','{:en}Our Goals{:}{:fr}Nos Buts{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','7-revision-v1','','','2021-01-23 00:17:44','2021-01-22 19:17:44','',7,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/7-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (205,1,'2021-01-23 00:21:07','2021-01-22 19:21:07','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>From the outset over the past 2 1/2 years, we have had 29 peers join our group and help advocate for our important mission. Earlier in 2019, we had another recruitment and expansion followed by further training for newer members.\n                            We had an initial training in March 2017 from Sylvain D\'Auteuil who trained, led and guided our group until we became more autonomous in 2018. He continues to support and mentor our group. We have also greatly benefited the\n                            past year from the support of a community organizer from the CIUSSS-ODI.</p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Depuis notre début et au cours des deux dernières années et demie, 29 pairs ont rejoint notre groupe et nous ont aidés à défendre notre mission importante. À la suite de nos activités de recrutement en début 2019, nous avons eu\nune expansion suivi d’une formation supplémentaire donnée aux nouveaux membres. En Mars 2017, M. Sylvain d\'Auteuil nous a aussi donné notre formation initiale pour ensuite diriger et guider notre groupe jusqu\'à ce que nous\ndevenions plus autonomes en 2018. Il continue à nous fournir son support et ses conseils. Nous avons également grandement bénéficié cette année dernière du soutien d\'une organisatrice communautaire du CIUSSS-ODI.\n<br>\n<br> Certaines de nos implications comprennent: membres participants à la Table de Concertation en Santé Mentale de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île, membre des conseils d\'administration de divers organismes et associations de santé mentale,\nmembre des sous-comités de la primauté de la personne du CIUSSS-ODI. en plus de participer à divers comités (comme ceux de HGL et de TQSOI, entre autres) et de faire du bénévolat dans la communauté. Nous avons participé à des\ndocumentaires, réalisé des entrevues à la télévision (CTV News Montréal, CBC Our Montréal, Global), à la radio (CJAD, CBC Montréal) et dans les journaux (Cité Nouvelles). Nous avons également fourni des témoignages et des lettres\nde soutien à nos organisations partenaires.\n<br>\n<br> Le Groupe Citoyen de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île a été crée en mars 2017 à partir du désir de la communauté santé mentale locale de faire entendre la voix des citoyens et de les impliquer dans leur communauté. À l\'initiative de\nla Table de concertation en santé mentale de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île (qui regroupe toutes les organisations locales de santé mentale et les organisations intéressées de l\'Ouest de l\'Île), les ressources nécessaires ont été investies\nafin de créer un comité régional permanent de citoyens dont les clients de leur région sont les seuls membres. C\'est devenu le Groupe Citoyen de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}','{:en}Our Members{:}{:fr}Nos Membres{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','44-revision-v1','','','2021-01-23 00:21:07','2021-01-22 19:21:07','',44,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/44-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (206,1,'2021-01-23 22:47:34','2021-01-23 17:47:34','{:en}<!-- wp:html -->\n                        <br>\n                        <br>\n                        <p>Thank you for your consideration in supporting us and an important cause. Your donation will go towards furthering our mission &amp; goals, to help raise awareness and fight the stigma of mental illness, and to expand &amp; provide more\n                            outreach for our group, and also to further train new members to our group to use our collective voice in the community!\n                            <br>\n                            <br> Donations to our West Island Citizens Group can be made via our fiduciary, PCSM, who will issue tax receipts.\n                            <br> Please make cheques payable to \'Community Perspective in Mental Health\', and\n                            <i>please clearly write \'For the West Island Citizens Group\' on the cheque memo line.</i> Cheques can be given directly to one of our group members, or can be mailed to:\n                            <br> WICG c/o Community Perspective in Mental Health\n                            <br> 15795, Boul. Gouin Ouest, 2nd floor,\n                            <br> Sainte-Genevieve, Que. H9H 1C5\n                            <br> This is PCSM’s contact info:\n                            <br> T 514-696-0972 F 514-696-0982\n                            <br> info@pcsm-cpmh.org / www.pcsm-cpmh.org / www.facebook.com/PCSMCPMH\n                            <br> Numero de charite 11945 0757 RR 0001 NEQ - 114 216 7262</p>\n<!-- /wp:html -->{:}{:fr}<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Merci de votre considération pour votre soutien à cette cause importante. Votre don servira à renforcer notre mission et nos objectifs, à contribuer à la sensibilisation, à lutter contre la stigmatisation de la maladie mentale,\n                            ainsi qu’à élargir la portée de notre groupe et à former davantage de nouveaux membres à utiliser notre voix collective dans la communauté!\n                            <br>\n                            <br> Les dons à notre Groupe Citoyen de l\'Ouest-de-l\'Île peuvent se faire à travers notre fiduciaire Perspective Communautaire en Santé Mentale, qui pourra émettre un reçu d’impôt de charité au besoin. Veuillez, s’il vous\n                            plait, faire votre chèque au nom de \'Perspective Communautaire en Santé Mentale\' et écrire clairement sur la ligne de notification du chèque: ‘Fonds pour le Groupe Citoyen de l’Ouest-de-l’Île’.\n                            <br> Les chèques peuvent être remis directement à l’un des membres de notre groupe, ou par envoi postal à:<br> GCOI a/s Perspective Communautaire en Santé Mentale<br> 15795, Boul. Gouin Ouest, 2ième étage,\n                            <br>Sainte-Geneviève, Que. H9H 1C5<br><br> Voici les coordonnées de PCSM:<br> T 514-696-0972 F 514-696-0982<br> info@pcsm-cpmh.org / http://www.pcsm-cpmh.org / www.facebook.com/PCSMCPMH<br> Numéro de charité 11945\n                            0757 RR 0001 NEQ# 114 216 7262\n\n                        </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->{:}','{:en}Donations{:}{:fr}Dons{:}','','inherit','closed','closed','','27-revision-v1','','','2021-01-23 22:47:34','2021-01-23 17:47:34','',27,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/27-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (208,1,'2021-01-25 02:03:01','2021-01-24 21:03:01','<!-- wp:shortcode -->\n[categoryposts]\n<!-- /wp:shortcode -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"sqbox2\">\n<br>                        <br>                        <p>Mars: Lancement du service de soutien en santé mentale \'Pairs Aidants J\'Écoute\' 1-800-425-9301                            <br>Mai: Mois de la sensibilisation à la santé mentale                            <br>4-10 Mai: Semaine de la santé mentale                            <br>Jeudi 28 Mai 13h45: GCOI &amp; PCSM co-organisent un événement livres                            <br>vivants en ligne \'Ensemble à Distance avec PCSM &amp; GCOI!!\'. Pour plus d\'informations et pour                            <br>vous inscrire - https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/105033253288 ou visitez notre page Facebook</p>                        <br>\n</div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->','Nouvelles','','inherit','closed','closed','','116-revision-v1','','','2021-01-25 02:03:01','2021-01-24 21:03:01','',116,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/116-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (209,1,'2021-01-25 02:04:50','2021-01-24 21:04:50','<!-- wp:html -->\n<div class=\"sqbox2\">\n<br>                        <br>                        <p>Mars: Lancement du service de soutien en santé mentale \'Pairs Aidants J\'Écoute\' 1-800-425-9301                            <br>Mai: Mois de la sensibilisation à la santé mentale                            <br>4-10 Mai: Semaine de la santé mentale                            <br>Jeudi 28 Mai 13h45: GCOI &amp; PCSM co-organisent un événement livres                            <br>vivants en ligne \'Ensemble à Distance avec PCSM &amp; GCOI!!\'. Pour plus d\'informations et pour                            <br>vous inscrire - https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/105033253288 ou visitez notre page Facebook</p>                        <br>\n</div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->','Nouvelles','','inherit','closed','closed','','116-revision-v1','','','2021-01-25 02:04:50','2021-01-24 21:04:50','',116,'http://groupe-citoyen.local/116-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
